findings.lower_chest: Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion.

abdominal.hepatobiliary: Liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation throughout. No evidence of focal lesions or biliary dilatation. Gallbladder normal.
abdominal.pancreas: Normal attenuation throughout, no focal lesions or ductal dilatation.
abdominal.spleen: Normal size and attenuation, punctate splenic calcification likely related to prior granulomatous inflammation.
abdominal.urinary: Normal symmetric kidneys with no focal lesions or hydronephrosis.
abdominal.gastrointestinal: Appendix fluid-filled and dilated, maximum diameter 1.0 cm, mild wall thickening, wall hyperemia, adjacent fat stranding, trace free fluid, small linear appendicoliths.
abdominal.pelvis: Unremarkable urinary bladder and ureters, trace free fluid in pelvis.
abdominal.reproductive_organs: Hypoattenuating probable posterior uterine fundus fibroid measuring approximately 1.7 x 1.4 cm.
abdominal.vascular: No abdominal aortic aneurysm or atherosclerotic disease.
abdominal.bones: No evidence of worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture.
